verbose_text: On the basis of protein sequence identities, 19 pairs of putative paralogous GrTCP genes were identified, accounting for more than 70% of the entire GrTCP gene family and thereby supporting the hypothesis that putative gene duplication events are the main causes of the expansion of the GrTCP gene family.
